contributions.title: Heaven Sent
contributions.notes: Jad Fair's voice waxes between an unstable nasal falsetto and Lou Reed on the 64-minute title track. The rhyming stream-of-consciousness lyrics serve as a psychological chronicle of "falling in like" with someone. Nine additional tracks of sparse lo-fi music and Fair's near conversational observations are "remixes" of "Heaven Sent" and seem to tell the crumbling tale of like waning into disinterest. Spend an hour and some minutes in Jad's dream.
